-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-28/volpe-discusses-operating-the-boston-symphony-orchestra-audio-.html
Mark Volpe, managing director of the
Boston Symphony Orchestra, discusses operating the Boston 
Symphony Orchestra over the last 15 years, his search for the 
BSO's next musical leader, and Tanglewood's upcoming opening 
night. Volpe talks with Bloomberg's Vonnie Quinn on Bloomberg 
Radio's "The Hays Advantage."  
(Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 11:33
 